From Soup: 133 The element ( ) = 〈 |e | 〉 depends on the atomic configuration in which the one-electron states | 〉 and | 〉 are calculated. The configuration can be expressed in terms of normal coordinates and therefore we denote it by ( , ). Expanding the matrix element around = 0 and taking the leading terms one obtains for the transition | , 〉 → | , 〉 The first term shows that within Franck–Condon (FC) approximation the vibrational side peak intensities are determined by the overlaps 〈 | 〉. The second term describes the Herzberg–Teller effect which is usually very weak but can be important when the first term is negligible because of the symmetry reasons. In this work we nevertheless only focus on the first term.
